ERNEST WATSON v. LUCIUS S. STORRS et al., Receivers [No. 44,

October Term, 1934.]

Decided November 20th, 1934.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Urner, Adkins, Ofputt, Parke, and Sloan, JJ.

Howard A. Sweeten and Everett L. Buckmaster, with - whom were Benjamin N. Kline and Weinberg & Sweeten on the brief, for the appellant. James J. Lindsay, with whom was Philip S. Ball on the brief, for the appellees. Adkins, J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
